Elon Musk's SpaceX and Jeff Bezos' Blue Origin are among several US companies engaged in the private space business . 
 Blue Origin, LLC, keeps a low profile in Van Horn, Texas, a way station along Interstate 10 . 
 The highly visible SpaceX venture is at the opposite end of the state . 
 Bezos' wealth is estimated at nearly $35 billion, Musk's at $12 billion . 
 Both men hope to launch a new era of commercial space operations, in part by cutting costs through reusable rockets . 
 